┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         LOCAL vs REMOTE PARTITIONING                                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  LOCAL PARTITIONING
  ──────────────────
  Manager and all workers run in same JVM
  Workers use ThreadPoolTaskExecutor
  Good for: single-node, moderate scale (up to ~50M rows)

  REMOTE PARTITIONING
  ────────────────────
  Manager sends partition metadata via message queue
  (RabbitMQ / Kafka / ActiveMQ)
  Workers are separate JVM instances / pods
  Each worker picks up a partition message, processes it, sends reply

  Manager JVM                    Worker JVM-1
  ────────────                   ────────────
  Partitioner                    MessageChannel listener
      │                              │
      │──► partition-1 msg ──────────►│ process ids 1-1M
      │──► partition-2 msg ──────────►│ (different pod)
      │                          Worker JVM-2
      │──► partition-3 msg ──────────►│ process ids 2M-3M
      │
      ◄── completion replies ─────────
      │
  Mark step COMPLETE

  Good for: Kubernetes, massive scale (100M+ rows)

Job Types Beyond Migration
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   COMMON JOB PATTERNS                                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  1. SEQUENTIAL STEPS JOB
  ────────────────────────
