  ────────────────────────
  Job
   └── Step 1: Process file
          │
          ├── EXIT STATUS = "COMPLETED" ──► Step 2a: Archive file
          │
          ├── EXIT STATUS = "FAILED"    ──► Step 2b: Move to error folder
          │
          └── EXIT STATUS = "NO_DATA"  ──► Step 2c: Send empty-file alert


  3. PARALLEL STEPS JOB (independent steps run simultaneously)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Job
   └── Split (parallel flow)
          ├── Flow A: Migrate orders table
          ├── Flow B: Migrate customers table
          └── Flow C: Migrate products table
                │
                ▼ (all three complete)
          Step Final: Referential integrity check


  4. TASKLET JOB (non-chunk, single unit of work)
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Used for:
  - Truncating staging tables before load
  - Calling a stored procedure
  - FTP file download / upload
  - Sending HTTP request to external API
  - Archiving processed files to S3

  @Bean
  public Step truncateStep(...) {
      return new StepBuilder("truncate", repo)
              .tasklet((contribution, chunkContext) -> {
                  jdbcTemplate.execute("TRUNCATE TABLE staging");
                  return RepeatStatus.FINISHED;
              }, txm)
              .build();
  }

