Performance Tuning Checklist
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              DB MIGRATION PERFORMANCE TUNING                            │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CHUNK SIZE
  ──────────
  Too small (10)   → too many transactions → DB overhead
  Too large (10000)→ large rollback on failure, high memory
  Sweet spot       → 500 to 2000 rows per chunk (tune with profiling)

  READER OPTIMIZATION
  ────────────────────
  Use JdbcPagingItemReader with offset-free keyset pagination
  Add index on sort column (WHERE id > :lastId ORDER BY id)
  fetchSize on JDBC = same as chunk size → reduces round trips
  reader.setFetchSize(1000)

  WRITER OPTIMIZATION
  ────────────────────
  JdbcBatchItemWriter uses JDBC batch → single network round trip
  Disable indexes on target table before bulk load → re-enable after
  Use INSERT INTO ... ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE for idempotency
  Set target DB bulk insert buffer (innodb_buffer_pool_size for MySQL)

  CONNECTION POOL
  ────────────────
  HikariCP maxPoolSize >= (threadPoolSize + 2)
  Separate DataSources for source and target DB
  Set connectionTimeout, idleTimeout appropriately for long jobs

  PROCESSOR OPTIMIZATION
  ───────────────────────
  Cache lookup data in @PostConstruct (reference tables, enums)
  Avoid DB calls inside ItemProcessor — pre-load all reference data
  Use CompositeItemProcessor to chain processors cleanly

  MEMORY
  ───────
  Do NOT collect items in memory across chunks
  Each chunk is processed and discarded — GC stays healthy
  For very wide rows, reduce chunk size to manage heap pressure
  JVM heap: -Xms512m -Xmx2g for typical migration jobs
